Samsung is set to launch its next flagship smartphone on 25 February 2018. The company will hold a Galaxy Unpacked event at Mobile World Congress, which is set to kick off at 19:00 South African time. The invitation for the event features the number 9 – leading to speculation the company will announce the Samsung Galaxy S9 at the launch. Samsung has also included the text “The Camera. Reimagined”. “If a picture is worth a thousand words, the latest member of the Galaxy family has a lot to say,” said Samsung. “Samsung will showcase the next generation of Galaxy devices that reimagines the camera and redefines the way you share your moments.” Live streaming of the big event will be available on Samsung’s Galaxy page on 25 February. To sign up for the latest info on the new device and to watch the reveal live, you can register on Samsung’s website. 